Jedi 0.10.3

Using goto_assignments with follow_imports=True on `foo` in code like the following seems to navigate to `@decorator`

```
@decorator()
def foo():
    pass

foo()
```

I debugged it, and in this case in `filter_follow_imports` in jedi.api.__init__.py the name is an instance of TreeNameDefinition and calling name.infer() gives the wrapper function.

I changed the code to look like this, and it seems to improve things, but I haven't looked at the Jedi code enough to know if this is the right approach

```
        def filter_follow_imports(names):
            for name in names:
                if isinstance(name, imports.ImportName):
                    for context in name.infer():
                        yield context.name
                elif isinstance(name, TreeNameDefinition) and name.tree_name.get_definition().type in ('import_name', 'import_from'):
                    for context in name.infer():
                        yield context.name
                else:
                    yield name
```

